##Will House prices really come down after the epidemic?

Wechat, chinanewsweekly

Function introduction, here is "China News weekly" the head of the weekly gentleman, the influence has the influence you. Come with me to break through the fog, to find the truth, to watch the Times.

Whether the market is good or bad, the control of the property market will not be relaxed

After experiencing the hot and cold market in the first half of 2019 and the cold and cold market in the second half of 2019, many housing enterprises, investors and research institutions are predicting and analyzing what kind of surprise the "little spring" of the real estate market will bring in 2020.

Who Materials, the sudden new pneumonia stepped on the property market around the "brake. ". For a time, the property market around the "hibernation. ".

With the epidemic situation slowly under control, all over the resumption of work and rehabilitation. On March 11, the Shenzhen Municipal Bureau of Housing and Construction issued a circular on "measures to support real estate enterprises to speed up the resumption of work and production in response to the epidemic of new coronavirus pneumonia, " which clearly stated that, real Estate Development enterprises that have approved projects that have not been put on the market and have approved projects for sale are allowed to open on-site and open off-line sales offices depending on the situation of epidemic prevention and control.

Shenzhen's new deal, it seems to let the real estate to see a glimmer of hope. However, "thaw" after the property market will go where? As the most concerned topic of all parties, will house prices really fall?

It may not come again

Based on the Spring Festival home buying tide, the annual real estate market in the spring will appear a wave of sales season, the industry called "Small Yangchun. ". But the year of the Gengzi rat, so far has not let any real enterprises feel the warmth of spring.

The impact of the epidemic, the property market turnover continued to decline. According to the Chinese real estate decision-making data platform (CRIC) , the transaction volume of commercial housing in 88 key cities during the spring festival decreased by 63% compared with the 2018 Spring Festival holiday, with some third-and fourth-tier cities having no transactions and housing demand being suppressed in the short term.

According to the report on the impact of the epidemic on the real estate market and enterprises released by the Middle Finger Research Institute, nearly 80 percent of the 500 real estate managers believe that the epidemic has a more depressing effect on the property market than the 2003 SARS epidemic, the general development of the real estate market in 2020 forecast more pessimistic, more than half of the epidemic on the whole real estate market impact cycle for two quarters.

For the year as a whole, more than half of respondents expect sales to decline this year, with 25 per cent expecting a 10-30 per cent decline and 20 per cent expecting a 10 per cent decline. And from each big house enterprise release of january-february Sales Data, sales have varying degrees of decline.

At present, in addition to Evergrande Group's performance in February, according to statistics, R & F real estate, China Jinmao, Yuzhou real estate, Zhengrong real estate, Xincheng Holdings, Yagule group, these six enterprises sales fell more than 50% in February.

On March 2, Kerri released "China's top 100 real estate enterprises sales list for january-february 2020. " Based on the cumulative sales in january-february, the overall size of the top 100 real estate enterprises decreased by 23.8% year-on-year. Among them, there are more than 80 percent of the housing enterprises in February and the cumulative performance of the same month fell.

Kerri said the full-caliber sales of the top 100 housing enterprises in February were down 43.8 percent month-on-month and 37.9 percent year-on-year as a result of the outbreak. More than 80 percent of the top 100 housing enterprises in February and cumulative performance fell year-on-year. According to the supply and demand data of cities at the market level, among the cities monitored by CRIC, most cities had zero supply in February, and the turnover of key first-and second-tier cities dropped by 77% year-on-year, guangzhou, Ningbo, Chongqing, Xi'an, Nanning, Dalian, Wuhan and other cities in the single month of turnover fell more than 90% .

Figures released by the Shell Institute show that the real-time turnover of second-hand homes in Beijing fell by about 57.6 percent from January to February 2020. There has also been a fall in prices. The average transaction price of second-hand homes in Beijing was 54,115 yuan per square meter in February, down 8.6 percent month-on-month and 9.7 percent year-on-year, according to the Shell Institute. The average listing price for new homes was 57,790 yuan per square meter, extending the month-on-month decline to 3.9 percent.

At a time when the market is cold, nearly 60 city governments to maintain the stability of the property market. Among them, Zhumadian, Henan Province, issued "on further standardization to promote the steady and healthy development of the real estate industry, " 17 stable property market policies. Rules, with the provident fund to buy the first house, the minimum down payment ratio from 30% to 20% .

Just when everyone thought the real estate industry was about to recover, on February 28, the Henan Provincial Government interviewed the relevant responsible comrades of the Zhumadian Government and put forward clear requirements for the implementation of Zhumadian's recent real estate policy. The interview asked Zhumadian to maintain the housing non-speculation positioning, real estate as a means of short-term economic stimulus, to achieve the three stability goal.

March 7, Hainan Province, a piece of paper "limit purchase order" is to allow the entire market to start thinking about the real estate market in 2020.

The press conference held that evening in Hainan not only clearly stipulated that "commercial housing built on newly-sold land shall be subject to the existing housing sales system" in order to control the sale of short-term housing, and pointed out that "in Hainan has two or more sets of housing and permanent resident households in the province, to stop the sale of commercial housing and market-oriented commercial housing. ".

On the one hand, the decline in sales of real estate enterprises; on the one hand, the property market policies around the repeated shocks, the epidemic, the decline seems to have become part of the consensus, then house prices will go where?

"steady" is the word

People in the industry told China News weekly that in recent years, house prices have been in a "stable" state. Under state regulation, the Real Estate Market tends to calm down and is developing in a healthy and stable direction, bidding farewell to the "crazy period" of intense shocks, although the impact of the epidemic, january-february in some cities of low turnover, but the huge demand market is still to the industry bottom, it is unlikely to fall sharply in the near future.

Earlier, the Shell Institute released a report titled "Survey of Housing Consumer expectations in an epidemic" . Of those, only 8.5 percent said they had canceled a home purchase plan because of the outbreak, while 9.7 percent said they would stick to their original plan and more than 60 percent said they would delay buying a home.

It is not hard to see that, under the pressure of just-needed conditions, although 60% of respondents said they would put off buying a house, but did not give up the need to buy. A report released by the 58 Research Institute supported the figures, showing that the proportion of visits to temporary VR sales offices nationwide increased by 57.7 percent in January from the previous month, while visits to temporary VR sales offices in Beijing, Haikou and Taiyuan increased by more than 70 percent.

"after the end of the epidemic, during the backlog of demand for housing or will be released, " said 58 Anju Housing and Property Research Institute Branch Director Zhang Bo. It is not difficult to see that the SARS epidemic in 2003 will have a short-term impact on the real estate market, but the impact on the overall market is not obvious.

Affected by the SARS epidemic, China's GDP slowed down significantly in the second quarter of 2003, but after only one quarter it was quickly repaired. During this period, it mainly impacted the consumer sector, but the impact on real estate investment and volume and price was relatively small, real Estate Investment and sales area also only in March and April a certain degree of high-speed slowdown, but was restored in May, real estate investment and sales area growth in 2003 as high as 30% and 29% .

It should be noted that there are differences in macro-economic environment, policy environment and market environment between the two outbreaks. During the SARS epidemic in 2003, the monetary and property policies were relatively loose, and the real estate industry was supported by the policies. And after 2017, the real estate industry regulation, the implementation of stable land prices, stable house prices, stable expectations of long-term management control mechanism is still unswerving.

Recently, the People's Bank of China, in conjunction with the Ministry of Finance and the China Banking Regulatory Commission, held a symposium on financial support for the prevention and control of the epidemic and economic and social development and a teleconference on television and teleconference. The People's Bank also stressed in particular the need to insist on the positioning of houses for living, not for speculation, and the requirement that "real estate should not be used as a means of stimulating the economy in the short term" , to maintain the continuity, consistency and stability of the real estate financial policy.

The year 2020 will be dominated by stability.

Yan Yuejin, a financial commentator, said the Ministry of Housing and urban-rural development had recently reaffirmed its long-standing position that "houses are for living, not for speculation. ". This innovation is to emphasize the "long-term" , which shows that "housing is not speculation" positioning will not be affected by the market cycle. Whether the market is good or bad, the control of the property market will not be relaxed, which for 2020 and future development of the property market has a strong guiding significance. At the same time, the relevant policies also clearly put forward the development of long-term mechanisms and regulatory mechanisms, reflecting the guidance of the healthy and stable growth of the property market ideas.

In addition, on March 6, the Minister of Housing and urban-rural development, Wang Menghui, published a signed article in the People's Daily newspaper, saying that efforts should be made to stabilize land prices, stabilize house price expectations and maintain the steady and healthy development of the real estate market. Long-term adherence to the "house is used for living, not for speculation" positioning, continue to steadily implement the real estate market steady and healthy development long-term mechanism program, we will establish and improve institutional mechanisms for real estate regulation and control, including policy coordination, linkage between regulation and control, monitoring and early warning, public opinion guidance and market supervision.

According to the Central Bank's official website on February 20, LPR's latest offer is 4.05% for the one-year LPR and 4.75% for the five-year LPR. Previously, the one-year Lpr published on January 20,2020, was 4.15% and the five-year LPR was 4.8% .

LPR decline released what signal, does it mean that the real estate will rise again?

Dong Ximiao, a special researcher at the National Finance and Development Laboratory, said that the LPR decline may reflect two aspects of intentions. First, the impact of the epidemic on China's economy is short-term, so short-term interest rates have dropped more, focus on helping enterprises to tide over the current difficulties; over five years Lpr fell 5 basis points, not to the real estate market to ease the signal that the real estate regulation has not relaxed.
